<h1>Data visualization</h1>

<p>Just a collection of python scripts for visualizing data.</p>

<h1>Barycentric legend</h1>

<p>Creates a triangular legend based off barycentric coordinates, useful when mapping trivariate data
where variables always add to 1, like  <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Soil_texture">soil texture</a>.</p>

<p>Given pixel density and number of rows in the triangle create a RGB legend.</p>

<p>Scale:200 Rows: 10
<img src="examples/triangle_200_10.png" alt="" title="" /></p>

<p>Scale:200 Rows: 25
<img src="examples/triangle_200_25.png" alt="" title="" /></p>

<p>Scale:200 Rows: 50
